HEADWORD: Portoir
<hw>Por"toir</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF., fr.
<ets>porter</ets> to bear.]</ety> <def>One who, or that which, bears;
hence, one who, or that which, produces.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Branches . . . which were <qex>portoirs</qex>, and bare
grapes.</q> <rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portoise</ent>⟦br⟧
